---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="You Do Science: Feeling Sound Waves">
    <div class="activity-container">
        <h1>You Do Science: Feeling Sound Waves</h1>
        
        <div class="activity-intro">
            <h2>Can you feel sound waves?</h2>
            <p>In this hands-on activity, you'll explore how sound waves travel through air by feeling their vibrations. This activity complements what you learned in Experiment 9.1 about visualizing sound waves.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="materials-section">
            <h3>Materials Needed:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Large speaker or subwoofer</li>
                <li>Music player (phone, computer, etc.)</li>
                <li>Bass-heavy music</li>
                <li>Paper</li>
                <li>Small pieces of confetti or rice</li>
                <li>Adult supervision</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="procedure-section">
            <h3>Procedure:</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <h4>Setup your speaker</h4>
                    <p>Place the speaker on a flat surface. If using a subwoofer, make sure it's positioned upright.</p>
                    <div class="safety-note">
                        <strong>Safety Note:</strong> Keep the volume at a reasonable level to protect your hearing.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h4>Feel the vibrations</h4>
                    <p>Gently place your hand near (but not touching) the speaker. Play music with strong bass.</p>
                    <div class="observation-box">
                        <h5>Record your observations:</h5>
                        <textarea placeholder="What do you feel when the music plays? How does the feeling change with different volumes?"></textarea>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h4>Watch the paper dance</h4>
                    <p>Hold a piece of paper about 2 inches from the speaker while playing music.</p>
                    <div class="observation-box">
                        <h5>Record your observations:</h5>
                        <textarea placeholder="What happens to the paper? How does it move with different sounds?"></textarea>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h4>Confetti or rice experiment</h4>
                    <p>Place a few pieces of confetti or rice on top of the paper and observe their movement.</p>
                    <div class="observation-box">
                        <h5>Record your observations:</h5>
                        <textarea placeholder="How do the pieces move? What happens when you change the volume or type of music?"></textarea>
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="conclusion-section">
            <h3>Understanding Sound Waves:</h3>
            <div class="questions">
                <p>Based on your observations, answer these questions:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>How do your observations prove that sound travels in waves?</li>
                    <li>Why do you think you can feel the vibrations without touching the speaker?</li>
                    <li>How does this activity connect to what you learned about sound waves in Experiment 9.1?</li>
                </ol>
                <textarea id="conclusions" rows="6" placeholder="Write your conclusions here..."></textarea>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <style>
        .activity-container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 2rem;
        }

        .activity-intro {
            background: #f5f5f5;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 2rem 0;
        }

        .materials-section {
            background: #fff;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 2rem 0;
        }

        .materials-section ul {
            list-style-type: none;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .materials-section li {
            padding: 0.5rem 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
        }

        .procedure-section {
            margin: 2rem 0;
        }

        .procedure-section ol {
            list-style-type: none;
            counter-reset: step-counter;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .procedure-section li {
            counter-increment: step-counter;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            background: #fff;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 8px;
        }

        .procedure-section li::before {
            content: "Step " counter(step-counter);
            font-weight: bold;
            color: var(--accent);
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            display: block;
        }

        .safety-note {
            background: #fff3cd;
            border: 1px solid #ffeeba;
            color: #856404;
            padding: 1rem;
            border-radius: 4px;
            margin: 1rem 0;
        }

        .observation-box {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            border: 1px solid #e9ecef;
            padding: 1rem;
            border-radius: 4px;
            margin: 1rem 0;
        }

        textarea {
            width: 100%;
            min-height: 100px;
            padding: 0.5rem;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 4px;
            resize: vertical;
            margin-top: 0.5rem;
        }

        .conclusion-section {
            background: #fff;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 2rem 0;
        }

        h4 {
            color: var(--accent);
            margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .activity-container {
                padding: 1rem;
            }
        }
    </style>
</Layout>
